In what could alter the permutation for the 2019 general elections, 39 political parties are currently signing a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with the main opposition Peoples Democratic Party (PDP).  According to the organisers, the coalition is aimed at dislodging the governing All Progressives Congress (APC) from office in the next general elections.  The event is holding at the Shehu Musa Yar’Adua Centre, Abuja with PDP National Chairman Uche Secondus, PDP Governors and former Governors, PDP presidential aspirants, present and former National Assembly members among others at the crucial meeting.  The parties include the Reformed All Progressives Congress (R-APC) with its National Chairman Buba Galadima conspicuously present as well as embattled lawmaker Dino Melaye.  Other political parties that will sign the MoU include the Social Democratic Party (SDP), KOWA Party, Labour Party (LP), Young Democratic Party (YDP), Peoples Progressives Alliance (PPA), African Democratic Party (ADP), Peoples Democratic Congress (PDC), National Conscience Party (NCP), Democratic Alliance (DA), Democratic Peoples Congress (DPC) among others.   Details later…